entries.title: New York Gov. Kathy Hochul Abruptly Halts Manhattan Congestion Pricing
entries.description: The plan to charge drivers $15 to enter the city was set to take effect later this month.

entries.title: This Summer's Best Iced Teas Come in Bright Colors and Bold Flavors
entries.description: Iced tea needn’t be a watered-down version of the hot kind. Here, the bags worth brewing this summer, in intense flavors and equally vivid hues.

entries.title: Boeing's Starliner Launches NASA Astronauts After Setbacks and Delays
entries.description: The spacecraft is expected to reach the International Space Station Thursday and return to Earth next week.

entries.title: Hunter Biden's Ex-Wife Testifies About His History of Drug Use
entries.description: Prosecutors try to convince jurors that the president’s son lied about his drug use during a 2018 firearm purchase.

entries.title: Google Parent Alphabet Poaches Eli Lilly Finance Chief Ashkenazi
entries.description: Ashkenazi will succeed Ruth Porat, who was previously named president and chief investment officer.

entries.title: Ukraine Strikes Inside Russia With U.S.-Made Missiles
entries.description: The Biden administration first permitted such strikes last week, to help Ukraine repel a Russian offensive targeting Kharkiv.

entries.title: Virginia Passed a Law Adopting California's EV Standards. Now It Wants Out.
entries.description: Gov. Glenn Youngkin, a Republican, says it is “fundamentally wrong” for the government to tell people what kind of car they can buy.

entries.title: Vice's Shane Smith Is Returning to the Spotlight, With Few Regrets
entries.description: The co-founder of the one-time media juggernaut will host a new podcast with Bill Maher as a recurring guest.

entries.title: Schumer Forces Republicans to Take Sides on IVF, Contraception
entries.description: The Senate Democratic leader sees the fallout from 2022 abortion ruling as galvanizing voters again this fall.

entries.title: 80 Years After D-Day, France Examines the Trauma of Allied Bombings
entries.description: Macron commemorates the more than 50,000 French civilians killed in U.S. and British air raids during World War II.

entries.title: 'The Catalyst' Review: The RNA Renaissance
entries.description: Once dismissed as a molecule of minor importance, RNA now appears to be the apotheosis of everything essential to life.

entries.title: Ike Returns to Normandy
entries.description: In the 1964 anniversary film, Eisenhower recounts the D-Day invasion for CBS’s Walter Cronkite.

entries.title: India's Election Humbles Narendra Modi
entries.description: He expected a blowout, but his party lost more than one-fifth of its seats and its outright majority.

entries.title: U.N. Atomic Agency Censures Iran Over Nuclear Actions Despite Retaliation Threat
entries.description: Tehran has threatened to respond to the rebuke by further scaling down oversight of its nuclear activities.

entries.title: Pro-Palestinian Protesters Arrested at Stanford After Takeover of President's Office
entries.description: Some demonstrations are persisting at American universities as school year winds down.

entries.title: Comex Gold, Silver Settle Higher
entries.description: Comex gold settled 1.2% higher and silver rose 1.6%. Both metals have been up two of the past three sessions.

entries.title: Bank of Canada Cuts Rates to Become First G-7 Central Bank to Ease Policy
entries.description: The Bank of Canada cut its main interest rate by a quarter percentage point, becoming the first Group of Seven central bank to provide rate relief after global policymakers aggressively increased borrowing costs to tame inflation.

entries.title: U.S. Spy Chief to Reinforce Biden's Push for Gaza Cease-Fire in Qatar Talks
entries.description: The renewed effort comes after President Biden laid out a three-phase deal that would free Israeli hostages in return for Palestinian prisoners.

entries.title: Rubio's Restaurants Files for Bankruptcy With Plans to Sell Chain
entries.description: It is the second chapter 11 filing in less than four years for the operator of Rubio’s Coastal Grill.

entries.title: Digital Freight Startup Transfix Sells Brokerage Unit
entries.description: The company, which had planned a public listing until a freight demand downturn hit the sector, will focus on its software business.
